5:
We're pretty far from any
civilization... Are you positive she
lives out here?
8:
Very. I'm certain she'll help us once
we find her...
11:
The local folktales claim she's an
ancient witch who lives at the top of
an abandoned tower.
19:
Thank you for your aid, Ruelle the
Looking Glass Witch.
23:
If I may, Champion... If you're truly
who you say you are...
26:
Would you save me if I were ever in
trouble?
30: Of course! I would come running.
42: So we meet again, my champion—
57:
Your aura tells me you're the
champion, but... you're smaller than I
remember...
68:
Y-you've got to be kidding meee!
You promised you'd save meee!
77:
I didn't do anything! At least, I don't
remember doing anything...
82: I'm cursed by this magic mirror!
85:
I got caught up in my father's weird
ritual and was sealed into the mirror
for who knows how many hundreds
of years!
89:
Then a champion came along... and
I thought I would finally be freed!
93:
But now that same champion who
promised me aid is some stupid
rabbit without any powers!
98:
W-wait, did you say this mirror was
cursed? Where have I heard this
before—
103:
What kind of champion fails his
damsel in distress?!
107: Oh... So that's how it is... Oof...
112:
I-I'm sorry... I'm not sure what I did,
but I apologize! So please, calm
yourself...
118:
What's the point of apologizing if
you don't even know why you're
doing it? *wail*
124:
The world's going to be destroyed?
Huh. My condolences. Anyway, not
my problem.
128:
A-are you sure you should be so
flippant about it? You'll be in trouble
too if everything is ruined!
132:
I'm already cursed. How much
worse could things get?
140: Are you implying it's my fault?!
143:
Yeah... Even if you didn't mean to,
you're the reason she's upset.
147:
...I guess it would suck to die before I
meet my soulmate.
150:
Fine. This world's done for, without a
doubt. Right?
157:
Which means that I'll never meet
another champion if I stay here,
right?
166:
Then there's no point staying in this
awful place!
168:
If you won't be the one to free me
from the curse, then at least take
me someplace where I can meet a
different champion!
172:
A different champion? That might
be... a little difficult...
177:
Ugh, all right! It doesn't have to be a
champion—I'll take any Prince
Charming I can get!
181: What if you came to Starview Village?
185: Do you have Prince Charmings there?
189:
It is a place where many people
come and go, so there's a chance
you might meet the one you're
seeking.
192:
I wouldn't be surprised if we already
have a curse breaker waiting
around.
196:
Well, what are we standing around
for? Take me there, ex-champion.
199:
You're going to make up for all the
time I spent waiting for you. Promise
me.
212:
Maybe you were my Prince
Charming all along.
223:
Sheesh, this thing was way heavier
than I thought it'd be...
227:
Did you really need us to drag it
here?
230:
Of course I did. The mirror's the
source of my powers.
234:
A gathering place situated between
many worlds... Surely I'll meet the
one who can free me here!
244:
Thanks. I can't wait to see everything
it has to offer!
